{
  "texts": [
    "Some intuitive visual examples of model interpretation to improve are also given for the misclassified samples and poorly segmented regions.",
    "In this way, it ensures transparency and provides a further roadmap for refinements.",
    "The analysis of misclassified samples and poorly segmented regions uncovers the major challenges which the PolyNetDWTCADx framework faces.",
    "Misclassifications were found with classes whose features overlap; for example, polyps vs. hemorrhoids, where the subtle changes of texture and shape in every class made it quite problematic to delineate one against the other.",
    "This observation is well illustrated by how all samples from Class 7 (polyps) were often categorized as Class 8 (adenoma) since they exhibited practically similar appearances."
  ]
}